  <hr>

  <!-- TEXT TREATMENTS -->
  <h2>Text Treatments</h2>

  <p><strong>Bold (semibold)</strong> for emphasis within a sentence. <em>Italic</em> for titles, foreign words, or gentle stress. <mark>Highlighted text</mark> uses the yellow accent — for truly important moments. <code>Inline code</code> for technical references.</p>

  <p>A <a href="#">link</a> underlined in yellow, which highlights the full word on hover. <a href="#" class="visited">Visited links</a> are slightly muted.</p>

  <p>Selecting any text on this page highlights it in <span style="background: var(--color-accent); color: #1a1a1a; padding: 1px 4px;">yellow</span> — try it.</p>

  <hr>

  <!-- DROP CAP -->
  <h2>Drop Cap</h2>
  <p>First paragraph of every article gets a drop cap.</p>

  <div class="article-body" style="margin-top: var(--space-md);">
    <p>Every article opens with an oversized first letter set in EB Garamond Semibold — a nod to illuminated manuscripts and old-world editorial design. It anchors the reader at the start of the piece without requiring any other decoration.</p>
  </div>

  <hr>

